
Summary of All Changes
Phase 1: Local PDF Storage
src/lib/scraper/pdf-storage.ts (NEW) — savePdfLocally() saves PDFs to data/pdfs/{board}/{grade}/, saveExtractedText() saves .txt alongside, readExtractedText() reads back for verification
CBSE scraper updated — after downloading each PDF, saves it locally before AI parsing
.gitignore — added data/pdfs/
Phase 2: Content-to-PDF Provenance Mapping
src/lib/scraper/syllabus-inserter.ts rewritten — accepts SourceContext with pdfPath, textPath, pdfUrl, aiModel, scrapeJobId, boardCode. Writes all this to subjects.metadata and chapters.metadata JSONB
Sets reviewStatus: "pending" on every newly scraped subject
Returns subjectId for downstream tracking
Explorer API updated — reads provenance directly from subjects.metadata instead of querying pipeline logs (faster, more reliable)
Phase 3: Sanity Check — Side-by-Side Verification
/curriculum/verify/[subjectId] page — Full-screen two-panel layout:
Left panel: Raw extracted PDF text (from local .txt file) in monospace with search highlighting
Right panel: Parsed content tree (chapters → topics) — click any chapter/topic title to highlight it in the raw text
Source info bar: AI model, parse date, original PDF link, local path, job ID
Review actions: Approve (green), Reject (red), Flag for Re-parse (orange) — updates reviewStatus in metadata
Search input highlights matching text in both panels
GET /api/admin/curriculum-explorer/[subjectId]/verify — Returns raw text + parsed content + metadata
POST /api/admin/curriculum-explorer/[subjectId]/review — Approve/reject/flag with reviewer tracking
Phase 4: Inline Scrape from Explorer
Tree View — When a grade is expanded and incomplete, shows a "Scrape Class X" button inline that triggers POST /api/admin/scrape-jobs with board+grade pre-filled
Grid View — Each subject card with content shows "Verify parsed content" link
Both views link to the verify page per subject
Phase 5: Student Content Pipeline Prep
All scraped content gets reviewStatus: "pending" in metadata
Admin approval flips to "approved" — this is what students will see
Full provenance chain: PDF URL → local PDF path → extracted text path → AI model → scrape job ID → parsed subject/chapters/topics
Every entity traceable back to its source PDF

Complete Content Flow
Admin triggers scrape → CBSE page fetched → PDFs found
→ PDF downloaded + saved locally (data/pdfs/CBSE/10/Arabic.pdf)
→ Text extracted + saved (data/pdfs/CBSE/10/Arabic.txt)
→ AI parses text → Zod validates → DB insert with provenance metadata
→ Admin opens Curriculum Explorer → sees subjects with completion %
→ Clicks "Verify" → side-by-side comparison
→ Clicks chapter title → highlights in raw text for accuracy check
→ Approves → reviewStatus = "approved" → ready for student Learn module
